data.name: DebugMultiButton.ToolTip
data.value: After using a skill, click this to perform a multi debug process of the OCR engine to ensure that the rectangle region and dots are set correctly. The OCR engine will run until it returns a value above the confidence threshold or iteration count exceeds 1000. You can also stop the process by clicking this button again. This will output some data to the textbox above and also create a debug image folder in the application directory. Note: Only the first iteration will save images.

data.name: DebugButton.ToolTip
data.value: After using a skill, click this to perform a debug process of the OCR engine to ensure that the rectangle region and dots are set correctly. The OCR engine will run once, returning a value ignoring the confidence threshold. This will output some data to the textbox above and also create a debug image folder in the application directory.

data.name: CooldownPropOCRRateTrack.ToolTip
data.value: The rate in ms at which OCR is performed. This affects how frequently the OCR engine will attempt to retrieve a cooldown value when skill is used. A lower value will be more CPU intensive. A higher value will be less accurate. Default: 100

data.name: CooldownBarsYOffsetTrack.ToolTip
data.value: The Y position offset for bars 2, 3 and 4 from bar 1. Set X Offset to 0 and this to any other value to list bars vertically. Set this to 0 and X Offset to any other value to list bars horizontally. This value is specific to the party size, so if you change the party size box, the value of this will reflect the change.

data.name: SelColourText.ToolTip
data.value: Set the colour/opacity of the currently selected character's cooldown bar when skill is on cooldown. An opacity value of 00 will hide the selected character's bar while on cooldown. Set to the same colour as FG1 Colour for no change.

data.name: SelTColourText.ToolTip
data.value: Set the colour/opacity of the currently selected character's cooldown text when skill is on cooldown. An opacity value of 00 will hide the selected character's text while on cooldown. Set to the same colour as FG1T Colour for no change.

data.name: LabelCooldownText2.ToolTip
data.value: This is a secondary orange rectangle region similar to the above but for characters like Mona where the original skill is replaced by her dash skill and the E skill is offset to the left. This region only gets checked if the 1st region does not return a valid cooldown time. If you are not using characters like Mona, just set this value to 0 to ignore the 2nd region entirely.

data.name: LabelCooldownText.ToolTip
data.value:
Define the position/size of a red rectangle region where the skill cooldown timer will be captured for OCR processing. You should ensure that the full cooldown timer is within the bounds of this region and not too close to the edges of the region.
If you have finished setting this up and correctly setup party numbers but you don't see any change to the bars when you use a skill: Switch character to stop the OCR attempt and reconfigure this region.

data.name: PartyNumComboBox.ToolTip
data.value: Select which party number dot to adjust the X/Y Pos of individually. This is necessary because the position of party numbers is different for different party sizes. Eg. "4 #1" will adjust position for the dot representing slot #1 when there are 4 characters in the party. You can also adjust the Bar Offset and Y Offset values for the selected party size.

data.name: PartyNumBarOffsetsTrack.ToolTip
data.value: A Y position offset of bar #1 from party numbers. This is necessary if you want bars to line up correctly with characters when there are fewer than 4 party members. This value is specific to the party size, so if you change the box on the right to a different party size, the value of this will reflect the change. This value is ignored if bar X Offset is not 0. Note: You may also need to adjust the bar Y Offset value below in order to line up the other bars correctly.

data.name: LabelPartyNumbers.ToolTip
data.value:
Define the position of party slot numbers denoted as small dots. You need to line these dots up to be in position of the white background of party slot numbers on the very right side of the game window.
To make sure you have set this up correctly, set "Sel. Offset" to something different and save configuration, and then try switching character. You should see the position of the bar for the selected character move.

data.name: DPIResolutionComboBox.ToolTip
data.value: You should only need to touch this if you're using desktop scaling and it could not be detected automatically. Select the same resolution that the game is set to in this box, then adjust the scaling with the slider. You can also use this to scale up values from a template if your in-game resolution is the same aspect ratio.

data.name: DPIScaleTrack.ToolTip
data.value: You should only need to touch this if you're using desktop scaling and it could not be detected or if your in-game resolution is the same aspect ratio as one of the templates. After modifying this, save config before making changes on the Manual Setup tab.

data.name: CooldownPropConfTrack.ToolTip
data.value: This determines how confident the OCR engine needs to be about an assumed cooldown detected. In most cases, accurate and fast results are produced at around 80% confidence. A lower value may result in cooldown being read incorrectly. A higher value will delay the cooldown output because the engine will continue to attempt reading until it's more confident. Default: 80%

data.name: CooldownPropTickTrack.ToolTip
data.value: The rate in ms at which frames are updated. This affects calculation of cooldown and how frequently the bars are updated. A lower value will be more CPU/GPU intensive. A higher value will be less accurate. Default: 10

data.name: CooldownPropPauseTrack.ToolTip
data.value: An amount in seconds to subtract the cooldown by whenever the game state is paused. This is necessary because the actual cooldown starts updating after an unpause before it can be re-detected. Default: 1

data.name: CooldownPropOverrideTrack.ToolTip
data.value: The max cooldown time in seconds to assume as overridable. Eg. For Fischl, when you use her skill it starts a 2sec cooldown. So this override should be set to 2.0 For multi-party events, override will be ignored if the character in the same slot as Fischl has a skill which starts a cooldown above 2sec. Default: 2

data.name: CooldownPropReapplyTrack.ToolTip
data.value: The minimum remaining cooldown time in seconds before attempting to use a skill will trigger cooldown detection. This is to make up for situations where the actual cooldown finishes before the assumed cooldown. This should not be more than Override. Default: 1

data.name: CooldownPropOffsetTrack.ToolTip
data.value: An amount to offset the assumed cooldown by in seconds. This may be necessary if you find the bar completing before/after the cooldown is actually complete. A positive value will add to while negative will subtract. Default: 0

data.name: AutoButton.ToolTip
data.value: Automatically set values depending on current game resolution. By default, only supports up to 1920x1080. Other resolutions can be added to GenshinOverlay.Templates.ini Newly added resolutions will require you to save config then reopen.

data.name: LabelCooldownOverrideL0.ToolTip
data.value:
Allows you to set a specific value for skill cooldown for each character. This is necessary for characters like Fischl where the actual cooldown doesn't start when the skill key is pressed and may only start after switching characters.
A value of 0 will disable override. An override value should be no less than the minimum defined by the "Override" property below.
